        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 12:22PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 1221 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Albertville, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Albertville, Boaz, Douglas, High Point, and Horton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
